LIBERTY is a compostition of completely unrestricted bezier curves.

NO UNIFORMITY is characteristic of the grid of circles with varied thicknesses, atop which lie curves of a randomized soothing pastel pallete.

FREEDOM granted by the number of randomized variables and large range guarantee a unique piece each iteration.


Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Soil Horizon Square #120
metadata.description:
A square version of the previous release of Soil Horizon. 

A Soil horizon is a layer parallel to the soil surface whose physical, chemical, and biological characteristics differ from the layers above and beneath.

Horizons are defined in many cases by obvious physical features, mainly color and texture.

Available for the Soil Horizon holders only.
2000x2000
Coded with p5js by @LESSLIE
___

Click the Open Live button
Press [S] to save the high-resolution version

metadata.name: MONOLITH #163
metadata.description:
Very limited facts are known about these strange monolithic structures. Black, rectilinear, similar to obsidian stone but made of strange materials. According to legend, an ancient civilization of high intelligence, called the Explorers of Latent Space, distributed hundreds of monoliths throughout time and space in order to study the behavior of species in the infinite Universe.

Some say that it is the divine intelligence of God. Others say that, in spite of their objectual and material condition, the monoliths possess their own consciousness and an intelligence beyond the natural and artificial. Their purpose or objective, to this day, remains a mystery.

_-_-_-_-_-_-_-_

this work is done only with code, using threejs and p5js
it might be a bit slow on low-end devices, be patient

metadata.name: ylb-mess-A #292
metadata.description:
With colors and shapes reminiscent of childhood LEGO explorations, 'ylb-mess-A' explores the assembly process in reverse, using recursive subdivision to create detailed structures instead of progressively building a complex structure brick by brick. Although the tools I use to explore and create have changed over the years, this piece reminds me of the natural creative curiosity that was instilled in me at an early age, for which I am incredibly grateful.

metadata.name: Dreamcatcher Forest #519
metadata.description:
"Dreamcatcher Forest" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022. The illustration in this work draws inspiration from Native American dreamcatchers, a protective talisman crafted from beautifully intricate patterns of woven thread, built from natural materials & colorful beads.

Dreamcatchers are used to protect dreamers while they sleep. Good dreams are able to slip through the web to meet the sleeper beneath, while bad dreams are trapped and prevented.

- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "P" key to export a print-quality image.
